subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 

Coelostoma martensi

Hebauer, 2002 (
Hebauer 2002
: fig. 7; 
Jia et al. 2014
: fig. 28) not only in the shape of aedeagus but also in the serial punctures on lateral elytra. It can be distinguished from the latter by median lobe widest subapically (widest medially in 

C. martensi

), paramere with a narrowed and rounded apex (apex of paramere broad and truncate in 

C. martensi

), elytron with ten rows of serial punctures (only with serial punctures sublaterally in 

C. martensi

).
